rComments: I enjoy history and loved the course. The exams and assignments were difficult but Prof. Barton took the time to meet with me a number of times to answer my questions and give feedback on my paper.

This was one of the best courses I've taken at U of T. I found Prof. Barton engaging and each lecture, although fast paced was well thought out and so interesting. I loved the film clips at the beginning.

I was very interested in 20th c europe before taking this course but prof Barton just ruined it. Her lectures were unorganized & sounded as if she was reading out of the textbook. There was an absurd amount of reading per week and weekly tutorial responses were required. Instructions on assignments were not clear. Most stopped going to lecture.

I really love history,  but Prof Barton made it dry. She lectures from a text book, doesn't put lecture slides up, and talks so fast it's nearly impossible to get everything she said. She also didn't tell us until the mid term that we didn't need to know anything from the text, just lectures. Waste of money and time. I dropped the course.
